<DocsLayout title="buoy skill" description="Generate design system skills for AI agents">
  <h1>buoy skill</h1>

  <p>
    Generate design system skills that AI agents can use to write compliant code.
    Creates structured markdown files optimized for Claude, GPT, and other LLMs.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <pre><code>buoy skill spill [options]</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Option</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>-o, --output &lt;path&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Output directory (default: .claude/skills/design-system)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--format &lt;format&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Skill format: claude, cursor, generic</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Example</h2>

  <pre><code>$ buoy skill spill

Generating design system skill...

Created:
  .claude/skills/design-system/
    SKILL.md
    tokens/_index.md
    tokens/colors.md
    tokens/spacing.md
    components/_inventory.md
    patterns/_common.md

Skill ready! AI agents will now follow your design system.</code></pre>

  <h2>Generated Files</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>SKILL.md</strong> - Main entry point with rules and triggers</li>
    <li><strong>tokens/</strong> - Token documentation by category</li>
    <li><strong>components/</strong> - Component inventory and usage</li>
    <li><strong>patterns/</strong> - Approved patterns and examples</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Using with Claude Code</h2>

  <p>After running <code>buoy skill spill</code>, Claude Code will automatically
  load the skill when building UI components.</p>

